You could let the app do the switching by tapping the triangle button on the Quotes page. If you feel tired of pressing the switch every time, please try this function. You could also change the time interval for Autoplay from the Settings page. Autoplay can be used at the same time as VoiceOver.

- Background and text design customization

Swipe to the right to go to the Design Settings page. You could change background image and text design to your liking. Go ahead and look for your favorite combination of background, text color, and text shadow color.

You could also save the image to your camera roll. Turn on your friend's "switch" by sharing your favorite quote. 

- Finally

There are more features than what we have explained above, and we are certain that this app will satisfy any quote lover.

Rememorate helps you remember the important people that you meet. It’s contact management and CRM app with a focus on easily retrieving and finding their info, even if you can’t remember their name.

When you want to remember someone, there are a bunch of ways you can find them -


Photo browse: look through your contact photos to see if you recognize the pic.

Map browse: find them on the map based on where you met.

Timeline browse: look through contacts by date and time that you met.

Text search: type in any names, keywords, or notes you remember.



Other Features -

Export and backup contacts with Dropbox.
Memory training game.
Business card scanning.
Note and keyword section for each contact so you can remember the personal details that can make or break a connection! 


Our mission -

We believe a contact management app should do more than just store your contacts. Over time it should help you remember more information about the important people in your life.

Rememorate stores your address book the same way your brain does, through associations. The more those associations are made, the more likely you are to remember someone without actively needing to reference them.

What we mean is, the more you use Rememorate to find who you are looking for, the less work you'll need to do to find them again. Rememorate helps your brain solidify those connections while keeping all their info ready just in case you need a quick reminder. 

Want to speed up the process? Rememorate subscriptions include a memory and brain training game using your contacts so you can keep everyone's names and faces fresh in your mind.

Rememorate is your personal contact assistant. It isn’t just a remember names app, it helps you remember the important details other address book apps can’t.


How does it work?

The first step to Rememorate someone is to take a photo. That photo will become a visual cue to help you remember that person -- it could be of the person, a selfie with you and the person, or even a photo of something that reminds you of the person/place/time.

From there, you can add any other contact info you might have, such as name, phone, email, notes, personal anecdotes, or any other info you want to remember later.

When you are ready to find your contact again, you can search your address book by photo, location, time, keywords, or all of the above!


Download now to see why Rememorate is the smartest way to manage your contacts.

results.description:
AroundThen makes business networking easier - allowing you to view, message and connect with nearby users on LinkedIn and Enterprise Social Networks, including Microsoft Office 365, Yammer and Salesforce Chatter.
 
From iOS 9 onwards, Bluetooth Low Energy is used to track the proximity of nearby AroundThen users, up to 50 feet away. All of the nearby AroundThen users are displayed in order of proximity, allowing you to view their profiles and connect immediately, or up to a week afterwards.
 
You can also check-in and share your location as an update on LinkedIn, Yammer or Chatter.
 
AroundThen is fully compatible with iPhone 4s and above, iPad 3 and above, and iPad Mini. Bluetooth Low Energy is not supported on earlier models, however the app will still function via location check-in.
